The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Flights hit
                                                                                                               Flights hit
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Dense fog disrupted flights at Calcutta airport for the second consecutive day on Sunday.        
	Two flights were diverted and 15 morning flights were delayed by an hour on an average as visibility dropped below 350 metres. Airport officials said flight operations were stalled from 11pm on Saturday to 6.35am on Sunday.        
	The Calcutta-London flight of British Airways was diverted to Hyderabad and JetLites Bangalore-Calcutta flight returned to Bangalore.        
	On Saturday, 25 flights were delayed.                                                                                                                                                                           
